Aim
To perform DNS enumeration using the dig utility in Kali Linux and retrieve A records, MX records, and Name
Server information of a target domain.
Introduction
DNS (Domain Name System) is used to convert domain names into IP addresses. DNS enumeration is the
process of collecting DNS information about a target domain such as IP addresses, mail servers, and name
servers.
The dig (Domain Information Groper) utility in Kali Linux is used to query DNS servers and retrieve domainrelated information for network analysis and security testing.
Procedure
Step 1: Install DNS Utilities
Open Kali Linux terminal and install DNS utilities:
sudo apt install dnsutils -y
Step 2: Verify dig Installation
Check whether dig is installed:
dig -v
Step 3: Retrieve A Record
Use the following command to get the IP address of a domain:
dig google.com
Step 4: Retrieve MX Record
Use the following command to get mail server information:
dig google.com MX
Step 5: Retrieve Name Server Information
Use the following command to get DNS name servers:
dig google.com NS
Implementation
Commands Used
dig google.com
dig google.com MX
dig google.com NS
Explanation
• dig → DNS query utility
• google.com → Target domain
• MX → Mail exchange records
• NS → Name server records
Output
google.com. IN A 142.250.183.14
google.com. IN MX 10 smtp.google.com
google.com. IN NS ns1.google.com
Result
Thus, DNS enumeration using the dig utility in Kali Linux was performed successfully and DNS records of the
target domain were retrieved.
